"""whittle — iteratively whittle down a set of failing tests.

Workflow:
    1. whittle init          Create/reset .whittle.json.
    2. whittle add <target>  Register test targets; discovers tests via TestX.
    3. whittle sync          Run tests; passing tests are removed from the set.
    4. whittle               Show what's left.
    Repeat 3-4 until all tests pass.

Commands:
    whittle init [--smoke]
        Create or reset the .whittle.json state file in the current directory.
        With --smoke, also add default smoke-test targets (hyperactor,
        hyperactor_mesh, and key Python test targets).

    whittle add [--include-flaky] <target> [<target>...]
        Add one or more buck test targets (e.g. fbcode//monarch/python/tests:foo
        or just python/tests:foo). Discovers all tests in each target via TestX
        and records them as pending. Flaky tests (per TestX) are excluded by
        default. Pass --include-flaky to include them.

    whittle sync [-k | --keep-going]
        Run all tests that are pending or failing. Stops on the first failure
        by default — use -k/--keep-going to run all tests regardless. Tests
        that pass are marked as passed and excluded from future syncs. Safe
        to Ctrl-C — partial results are saved and unfinished tests remain
        pending.

    whittle reset [--reinit]
        Reset all tests to pending. With --reinit, also re-enumerate tests
        from TestX (picks up new tests, drops removed ones, updates flaky
        list).

    whittle flake <test_name>
        Manually mark a test as flaky, excluding it from future syncs. The
        test name is the full "target - test_case" string as shown by
        `whittle`, e.g.:
            whittle flake monarch/python/tests:foo - test_foo.py::test_bar

    whittle skip <test_name>
        Skip a test temporarily. Skipped tests are not run by sync, but
        sync cannot succeed while skipped tests remain. Use this to pause
        a test and come back to it later.

    whittle unskip <test_name>
    whittle unskip --all
        Mark a skipped test as pending again. With --all, unskip all
        skipped tests.

    whittle pass <test_name>
        Manually mark a test as passed.

    whittle [--state=fail,skip,...] [-v]
        Print status: one line per test, tab-separated status and name.
        --state filters to specific states (comma-separated).
        -v adds a comment after each test with the buck command to
        reproduce it. Exits 0 if all tests pass, 1 if any are failing,
        pending, or skipped.

Output format:
    Lines starting with # are comments (diagnostics/summaries).
    Data lines are tab-separated: status<TAB>name.

    fail	monarch/python/tests:test_foo - test_foo.py::test_bar
    pass	monarch/python/tests:test_foo - test_foo.py::test_baz
    pending	monarch/python/tests:test_foo - test_foo.py::test_qux
    skip	monarch/python/tests:test_foo - test_foo.py::test_hard_one
    flaky	monarch/python/tests:test_foo - test_foo.py::test_flake

State is stored in .whittle.json in the current directory.

Example:
    ./whittle init --smoke  # init with default monarch smoke targets
    ./whittle sync          # runs tests, stops on first failure
    ./whittle sync -k       # run all tests, don't stop on failure
    ./whittle               # shows 3 failing, 500 passed
    # ... one test is flaky, not your problem ...
    ./whittle flake monarch/python/tests:foo - test_foo.py::test_flaky_one
    # ... one test is hard, skip it for now ...
    ./whittle skip monarch/python/tests:foo - test_foo.py::test_hard_one
    # ... fix the other failure ...
    ./whittle sync          # runs the 1 remaining failure, passes
    # ... come back to the skipped test ...
    ./whittle unskip --all
    ./whittle sync          # runs the skipped test

Composing:
    ./whittle | grep '^fail'           # just failing tests
    ./whittle | grep -v '^#'           # strip comments
    ./whittle | cut -f2 | sort         # sorted test names
"""

